<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Ok, I have heard an idea of this nature in the past, and i kinda liked it. i am trying to get some discussion going on it again on Pendragon and wanted opinions from here also.<P>The suggestion is this...<P>Make all Mez spells do exactly 1 point of damage. Regardless of any defenses or immunities, make the mezzed target lose 1 HP. It already adds us to their aggro so what could this accomplish?<P>1) Doing 1 HP means they are no longer at full health. Then heals can break the mez. Now if they are nto healed before the natural recovery kicks in and they are at full, the chance to break it will be lost. This is a nice balance. if a healer can react quickly, he can counter it, if not.... it will run its course.<P>2) Doing 1 measley point is all it woudl take for us to get our fair share off EVERY mezzed target in RvR. When the RPs are being split, our Mez will then count.<P>3) I think this happens already, but this will ensure any stealth class will lose their stealth upon mez since they have taken damage.<P>4) This one may not be liked by some... but it will prevent high level Sorcs from using Mez to baby sit and power level low levels. If we mez for them, we either get our fair share, or ruin the XP and loot for all. In light of the other benefits, I think this is MORE than fair a trade off.<P>So what does everyone think?<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
