I'd rather see them FIX other things rather than making changes to mez.  We already know the track record of inadverent changes.<P>&lt;Patch Notes 1.50&gt;<BR>When a player is mezzed, they will lose 1 hit point.  This will allow healers to cancel the affect.  If they regain the 1 point naturally, they will stay mezzed.<P>&lt;Patch Notes 1.50b&gt;<BR>While making the change to mez, it seems a bug was introduced that broke the mez when the hit points of the character was changed (ie. when they heal naturally).  We will fix this next patch day.<P>&lt;Patch Notes 1.51&gt;<BR>We are aware of the problem with mez breaking and the hit points changing.  We are firing the programmers because they didn't fix it like they were suppose to (not really, but we are pretty miffed!)<P>...Several months later...<P>&lt;Patch Notes 2.0&gt;<BR>We FINALLY fixed the problem with mez breaking when a player heals the hit point naturally...<P><BR>And if this is really that much of a problem, why not just add a cancel magic spell to counter the effects of mez?  Why not give tanks the ability to stun their realmmates with their shield to wake them up?  <P>Sorry i3ulls, the more I think about this solution the more I think it is a BANDAID fix to a problem people are complaining about (that of being mezzed).  I would rather be mezzed than one-shotted by snipers and bolt casters - I die way more by that than from being mezzed.<P>--------------------<P>Malachai Mindbender<BR>Enigmatic of Avalon<BR>Domus Caliburn - Guinivere
