Personally I think this is a great addition. When playing in the BG I typically mez first and then wonder what I can hit with my weak nukes.<BR>I dont think I would want to see the same feature on a debuff tho. That would break a root since they take 1 point of dmg right ?<P>There is a drawback to this tho right ? I use the EA mez almost exclusively with the single target mez for individual applications.  If I am called on to Mez a group of Mob's that are incoming I am typically chain casting my AE mez.  If more then half the Mobs continue towards us I already have the AE going again. If less then half are still coming I'll move a bit to intrupt and retarget the still incoming mobs. The issue tho is, if you do 1 point of DMG that will break all the Mez's again and hopefully they re-mez right ?   Right now if I chain mez and they resist the second one but were mez'd by the 1st one they still stay Mez'd since no damage occured.<BR>Or, am I totally off base ?  I dunno.<P>--------------------<P>No, that snapping sound is not your back.  It is your feeble soul...<BR>***********************************<BR>Taiju WillCrusher  30 Sorc / Lancelot - 26 Mind 14 Body<BR>Gulwyn MacFarlane  37 Cleric / Lancelot - 26 Rej 22 Enh 13 Smite
